      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUST PETTY CASH (11) finished off well last time out at Pinjarra but this looks to suit much better. This is easier today and the slight rise in trip looks right up her alley. May need some luck from the barrier, but if the breaks come then she'll be very hard to come out. ENCOSTA DE MONEY (4) never featured first-up before a much better effort here last time out, finishing 0.8L off the winner. Winkers replace the blinkers today and he rates highly on his most recently run. Third-up now and the rise in trip suits. Can go one better. LONG WAIT (6) was very good fresh when going in without a trial. She finished off nicely first-up over this track and trip and should be better for that run. Can put herself into the finish again. COSTA STAR (8) steps out in trip now off a better effort last time. Won't be far away. GILES (2) will benefit from the fresh run and can improve.",
